  • Enum Constant Details

    • STANDARD

      public static final ImageButton.ButtonState STANDARD

      Represents the standard ImageButton state.

      Details

      1. If the ImageButton is not disabled or otherwise being interacted with, the ImageButton state will be STANDARD.
      2. An ImageButton is in a standard state if...
        1. The mouse cursor is not hovering over the ImageButton.
        2. The ImageButton is not disabled.
      3. Analogous to default/vanilla.

    • HOVERED

      public static final ImageButton.ButtonState HOVERED

      Represents the hovered ImageButton state.

      Details

      1. An ImageButton is in a hovered state if...
        1. The mouse cursor is hovering over the ImageButton.
        2. The ImageButton is not disabled.

    • PRESSED

      public static final ImageButton.ButtonState PRESSED

      Represents the pressed ImageButton state.

      Details

      1. An ImageButton is in a pressed state if...
        1. The mouse cursor is currently pressed.
        2. The mouse cursor is currently within the bounds of the ImageButton.
        3. The ImageButton is not disabled.
        4. The ImageButton is toggleable and has been toggled on.
      2. If the mouse cursor is pressed while hovering over the ImageButton but is moved outside the ImageButton bounds, the ButtonState reverts to STANDARD.

    • DISABLED

      public static final ImageButton.ButtonState DISABLED

      Represents the disabled ImageButton state.

      Details

      1. An ImageButton is in a disabled state if...
        1. The ImageButton is disabled.
        2. In other words, if an ImageButton is disabled, the ButtonState will always be DISABLED.
